description:
ROBIN HOOD (1955)
Stars Richard Greene as Robin Hood, Archie Duncan (Little John), Alexander Gauge (Friar Tuck),  Bernadette O&#039;Farrell (Maid Marian) 

2x03. Blackmail  10/15/1956
By chance, a stranger hidden in a cart overhears a conversation between Robin and Marian. Is it enough to blackmail the outlaw of Sherwood Forest? Robin impersonates the Sheriff to turn the tables on the blackmailer.
  Guest star: Paul Eddington (Will Scarlet O&#039;Winchester), Ian Hunter (Sir Richard of the Lea), Patricia Burke (Lady Lincoln), Edward Mulhare (Ulf), Willoughby Gray (Bafe), Paul Hansard (Lescaux), Peter Bennett (III) (Steward), Shaun O&#039;Riordan (Guard) , Anthony Dawson (Lucas) 

2x19. The Final Tax  2/4/1957 
Tom Joyner, a serf, is supposed to be dying, and Sir Charles comes round to survey the possibilities of collecting the tax to which he is legally entitled if one of his villagers dies. But Friar Tuck has a plan to thwart the rascally bailiff.
  Guest star: Paul Eddington (Will Scarlet O&#039;Winchester), Paul Eddington (Sir Charles), Patricia Burke (Donia), Alan Edwards (Reeve) , Dennis Edwards (Bailiff), Fred Goddard (Tom Joyner), Barry Fennell (Simon), Jefferson Clifford (Retainer), Wilfrid Brambell (Ned)

2x20. The Ambush   2/11/1957 
Prince John is always trying to seize the English throne while King Richard is in the Holy Land. But there is someone with a better claim: Arthur of Brittany. Suppose, by some regrettable accident, that Arthur were killed?
  Guest star: Paul Eddington (Will Scarlet O&#039;Winchester), Peter Bennett (Edwin), Shaun O&#039;Riordan (Prince John&#039;s captain), Edward Mulhare (Courtier), Martin Lane (Spy) , Donald Pleasence (Prince John), Peter Asher (Prince Arthur), Dorothy Alison (Duchess Constance)
